WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: hr

00:00:08.710 --> 00:00:16.170
Dear viewers, welcome to another edition of the show without an address, the Hercegovna Info portal.

00:00:17.010 --> 00:00:20.930
Today we are again at the address of Chitluk, more precisely Padalovina.

00:00:22.270 --> 00:00:27.030
Our guest today, or rather the host, began his story right here,

00:00:28.250 --> 00:00:35.430
under this basket, across the basketball club Brotnjo, then Zagreb's Cibone, Megalex,

00:00:36.410 --> 00:00:42.270
and then to the biggest world scene of Los Angeles, the Lakers and the Clippers.

00:00:43.110 --> 00:00:47.910
Our guest today, or rather the host, the best Croatian basketball player, Ivica Zubac.

00:00:48.590 --> 00:00:51.770
Ivica, welcome to our home, or rather, welcome to your home.

00:00:52.610 --> 00:00:57.530
Thank you for taking the time for us, especially on a day like this.

00:00:59.990 --> 00:01:01.230
How is the rest in Hercegovina?

00:01:02.150 --> 00:01:06.590
Thank you for having me. It's always great here.

00:01:07.210 --> 00:01:11.330
It's always fun, it's always good to come and visit friends and family.

00:01:11.950 --> 00:01:16.770
I've spent some time where I grew up, where I'm from, and I'm always happy to come back.

00:01:17.130 --> 00:01:21.570
Thank you for having us on a day like this, because on a day like this,

00:01:22.350 --> 00:01:25.270
your great friend, our basketball player Luka Juricic, is getting married.

00:01:25.710 --> 00:01:30.250
Are the preparations for the last day harder than the whole season in the Clippers?

00:01:31.230 --> 00:01:34.290
No, it's not like that at all. We've been preparing for the whole week,

00:01:34.450 --> 00:01:39.690
partying, hanging out, so it's not that hard for me.

00:01:39.870 --> 00:01:41.710
But today is going to be hot.

00:01:43.370 --> 00:01:47.990
A few days ago, I was talking to our mutual friend, Ivo Juricic,

00:01:48.070 --> 00:01:50.510
and I told him that I often pass by your street,

00:01:50.710 --> 00:01:53.690
and he always tells me stories.

00:01:54.570 --> 00:02:01.650
What are your emotions when you come home from the U.S.

00:02:01.930 --> 00:02:04.870
and every time you look at this in front of your house?

00:02:05.650 --> 00:02:08.729
Well, I think this basket is full of memories.

00:02:09.530 --> 00:02:12.390
We grew up on this street, on this basketball court,

00:02:12.910 --> 00:02:16.910
we played every day, we learned the moves,

00:02:17.510 --> 00:02:23.270
we watched NBA videos, we tried to copy what was on this court,

00:02:23.270 --> 00:02:25.310
if it's possible to call it a basketball court,

00:02:25.310 --> 00:02:27.250
it's more of a street than a basketball court.

00:02:28.670 --> 00:02:33.350
I'm a bit sad that no one plays on this court,

00:02:33.890 --> 00:02:36.230
that you can't hear the ball or anything,

00:02:36.610 --> 00:02:39.750
but we really made the most of it.

00:02:41.010 --> 00:02:44.170
Your neighbor, who lives a bit further from your house,

00:02:44.350 --> 00:02:46.250
always says that when she goes to work,

00:02:46.330 --> 00:02:48.390
Ivica would be on the court all day.

00:02:48.390 --> 00:02:48.670
Did you have a lot of friends there?

00:02:49.870 --> 00:02:54.030
We were there a lot, we had a lot of kids in the village,

00:02:54.470 --> 00:02:56.470
we all grew up together for many years,

00:02:57.530 --> 00:03:01.750
we spent our days there, we all loved basketball,

00:03:02.170 --> 00:03:03.610
we grew up really well.

00:03:04.490 --> 00:03:07.850
Also, your brother was a great talent,

00:03:08.310 --> 00:03:11.570
but did you have a bigger love for basketball?

00:03:11.730 --> 00:03:16.760
I think it's possible, both of my younger brothers were talented,

00:03:16.760 --> 00:03:23.580
unfortunately, it didn't make a career out of basketball,

00:03:23.940 --> 00:03:27.600
but I think we had a lot of talent in our family,

00:03:27.660 --> 00:03:30.880
but you have to put a lot of things together to succeed.

00:03:33.020 --> 00:03:35.960
Did you ever dream that you could go from this court

00:03:35.960 --> 00:03:38.220
to the biggest world scene?

00:03:39.660 --> 00:03:42.020
We always dreamed, we all dreamed,

00:03:43.040 --> 00:03:45.420
but it had to be a bit realistic,

00:03:47.600 --> 00:03:52.000
I never expected to get to where I am now,

00:03:52.020 --> 00:03:54.080
there were always dreams and wishes,

00:03:54.320 --> 00:03:56.840
but I was always a bit realistic,

00:03:57.120 --> 00:04:00.040
my goal was to play for the seniors of Brotnjak,

00:04:00.640 --> 00:04:04.720
and as I walked step by step,

00:04:04.920 --> 00:04:06.300
that goal was getting higher and higher,

00:04:06.760 --> 00:04:09.040
and now I am where I am.

00:04:09.480 --> 00:04:14.960
Did you watch our Zoran Planinča,

00:04:14.960 --> 00:04:15.680
who is also here,

00:04:15.680 --> 00:04:18.019
was he a role model for you?

00:04:22.140 --> 00:04:24.700
I think that Zoka was the reason

00:04:24.700 --> 00:04:28.760
why a lot of us started playing basketball here.

00:04:28.940 --> 00:04:30.360
He was always drafted,

00:04:32.800 --> 00:04:35.160
we didn't know anything about basketball,

00:04:35.860 --> 00:04:40.080
and we wanted to copy what he did,

00:04:40.380 --> 00:04:41.240
and he was always there,

00:04:41.240 --> 00:04:42.600
every summer when he had time,

00:04:42.840 --> 00:04:43.780
he played basketball with us,

00:04:44.840 --> 00:04:46.440
and that meant a lot to us,

00:04:48.720 --> 00:04:52.240
and it gave us the motivation to do it.

00:04:55.660 --> 00:04:56.540
This is Juca,

00:04:57.040 --> 00:04:58.900
where it all started,

00:04:59.000 --> 00:05:00.380
in front of the house,

00:05:00.940 --> 00:05:03.880
and now we are in the house.

00:05:05.080 --> 00:05:06.560
How much do you like to come here,

00:05:06.680 --> 00:05:09.080
how much do you like to sleep in your own bed?

00:05:11.240 --> 00:05:12.540
How much do you miss your mom's food?

00:05:14.760 --> 00:05:15.920
A lot, a lot.

00:05:16.060 --> 00:05:19.740
That's the only thing I miss in America,

00:05:20.760 --> 00:05:22.280
family, friends,

00:05:22.620 --> 00:05:24.020
the atmosphere here,

00:05:24.900 --> 00:05:25.440
the kitchen,

00:05:28.360 --> 00:05:29.240
socializing,

00:05:29.940 --> 00:05:32.240
that's something I don't have there,

00:05:32.800 --> 00:05:34.700
and I can't have there,

00:05:35.380 --> 00:05:37.940
and that's why every summer,

00:05:37.940 --> 00:05:39.680
whenever I can, I come back,

00:05:40.660 --> 00:05:41.860
it's always the best,

00:05:42.180 --> 00:05:43.900
and I really enjoy it,

00:05:44.040 --> 00:05:45.040
every time I'm here.

00:05:45.320 --> 00:05:47.800
I had a chance to hang out recently,

00:05:48.220 --> 00:05:52.660
we had one in your grandfather and grandmother's house,

00:05:52.820 --> 00:05:54.320
your cousin Nikola's,

00:05:54.320 --> 00:05:56.140
and your father gave us some wine,

00:05:56.880 --> 00:06:00.660
I heard that's a favorite place for you,

00:06:00.660 --> 00:06:01.340
when you come here.

00:06:01.360 --> 00:06:03.560
Yes, I can tell you,

00:06:04.700 --> 00:06:07.700
we spend almost every evening there,

00:06:07.940 --> 00:06:09.580
we get together there,

00:06:09.920 --> 00:06:12.040
a few friends from the village,

00:06:12.700 --> 00:06:14.360
from Chitluka, Medjugorje,

00:06:14.740 --> 00:06:16.500
and that's where we usually hang out,

00:06:17.380 --> 00:06:18.440
we eat car,

00:06:19.600 --> 00:06:21.700
we drink a little wine,

00:06:23.140 --> 00:06:24.020
we hang out,

00:06:24.740 --> 00:06:25.720
that's where we enjoy,

00:06:26.040 --> 00:06:29.540
that's where something happens every evening,

00:06:29.740 --> 00:06:31.180
someone organizes something,

00:06:31.500 --> 00:06:34.760
and that's the place where we get together.

00:06:35.260 --> 00:06:37.220
Your father makes great wine,

00:06:37.940 --> 00:06:40.960
the whole family is working on it,

00:06:41.800 --> 00:06:42.260
so tell me,

00:06:42.440 --> 00:06:44.560
what's your job when it comes to wine?

00:06:45.360 --> 00:06:46.660
At this stage,

00:06:46.980 --> 00:06:48.840
I'm just tasting it.

00:06:51.660 --> 00:06:53.080
It's a family business,

00:06:53.260 --> 00:06:53.680
it's been going on for a long time,

00:06:54.360 --> 00:06:55.880
a few generations,

00:06:56.960 --> 00:07:00.160
and now mostly my father works on it,

00:07:00.620 --> 00:07:01.660
my brothers help,

00:07:01.940 --> 00:07:03.420
the rest of the family does the same.

00:07:04.660 --> 00:07:06.420
Unfortunately, I'm not there,

00:07:06.420 --> 00:07:08.240
when I was younger,

00:07:08.440 --> 00:07:10.440
that's where I knew how to be,

00:07:10.560 --> 00:07:10.880
to be in the fight,

00:07:11.580 --> 00:07:13.560
to help around Sitnica,

00:07:14.340 --> 00:07:15.980
and when it was time to step on the gas,

00:07:16.180 --> 00:07:16.720
Grozdy,

00:07:16.960 --> 00:07:18.980
but lately,

00:07:19.600 --> 00:07:21.240
it's really just tasting,

00:07:21.860 --> 00:07:23.140
that's where I am,

00:07:23.420 --> 00:07:24.440
that's where I help.

00:07:24.940 --> 00:07:25.500
That's where you're a ball,

00:07:25.540 --> 00:07:26.460
like in basketball, right?

00:07:26.640 --> 00:07:28.380
That's where I'm solid.

00:07:30.140 --> 00:07:32.680
Everyone has a break,

00:07:33.880 --> 00:07:34.600
it passes quickly,

00:07:36.420 --> 00:07:36.780
and that's where you arrive.

00:07:37.540 --> 00:07:38.900
I've been here for a day,

00:07:39.040 --> 00:07:41.360
tomorrow I'm going to Zagreb,

00:07:41.500 --> 00:07:43.560
I'm starting training there,

00:07:43.820 --> 00:07:44.720
next week,

00:07:46.580 --> 00:07:49.540
I have a long summer ahead of me,

00:07:49.800 --> 00:07:52.760
but I've set some new goals

00:07:52.760 --> 00:07:54.360
for the next season,

00:07:54.760 --> 00:07:56.320
and that's the only thing I can do

00:07:56.320 --> 00:07:57.140
all summer,

00:07:59.240 --> 00:08:01.460
there's the best weather,

00:08:01.800 --> 00:08:03.240
I'm a coach there,

00:08:03.440 --> 00:08:05.720
so I'm mostly in touch

00:08:05.720 --> 00:08:07.120
with Zagreb,

00:08:07.220 --> 00:08:08.700
I go to Slavonia,

00:08:08.720 --> 00:08:09.660
sometimes to Ženina,

00:08:10.020 --> 00:08:12.420
and that's where I've been all summer.

00:08:12.740 --> 00:08:14.480
Speaking of last season,

00:08:14.560 --> 00:08:15.300
it was a great season,

00:08:15.420 --> 00:08:15.740
and for you,

00:08:15.820 --> 00:08:17.420
maybe the best NBA season,

00:08:18.180 --> 00:08:20.000
when it comes to points,

00:08:20.780 --> 00:08:21.460
and the number of jumps,

00:08:22.520 --> 00:08:24.000
59-0-0.

00:08:25.660 --> 00:08:27.380
The best, for sure,

00:08:27.740 --> 00:08:31.200
but I think it's a normal development

00:08:31.200 --> 00:08:32.080
of my career,

00:08:32.220 --> 00:08:33.179
I expected it all,

00:08:35.720 --> 00:08:36.860
everyone's talking about it,

00:08:37.480 --> 00:08:39.419
I think it was a great season,

00:08:39.640 --> 00:08:40.980
but it's normal for me,

00:08:41.000 --> 00:08:41.799
I'm working for it,

00:08:42.280 --> 00:08:43.039
I've set those goals,

00:08:44.520 --> 00:08:45.620
and it's normal for me,

00:08:45.960 --> 00:08:47.700
I came there early,

00:08:48.880 --> 00:08:51.040
people expected it from the start,

00:08:51.180 --> 00:08:52.140
I don't know what's going to happen,

00:08:52.560 --> 00:08:54.080
but I went step by step,

00:08:54.320 --> 00:08:55.120
I worked there,

00:08:55.440 --> 00:08:56.900
I came to a position

00:08:56.900 --> 00:08:58.900
where I have an important role,

00:09:00.060 --> 00:09:01.560
where I know who I am,

00:09:01.660 --> 00:09:03.900
what I do, what I can do,

00:09:05.720 --> 00:09:06.800
and it all worked out,

00:09:07.560 --> 00:09:08.500
it turned out great,

00:09:08.620 --> 00:09:09.360
there were no injuries,

00:09:10.240 --> 00:09:12.940
and it was a great season,

00:09:13.140 --> 00:09:13.740
I'm satisfied,

00:09:14.520 --> 00:09:16.940
and I hope with a full summer of work

00:09:16.940 --> 00:09:17.640
and rest,

00:09:18.420 --> 00:09:21.040
that I'll raise it to a higher level.

00:09:21.760 --> 00:09:22.500
At the end,

00:09:22.900 --> 00:09:23.900
you lost to Denver

00:09:23.900 --> 00:09:26.080
in the deciding game,

00:09:27.380 --> 00:09:28.860
how did you see that series,

00:09:29.140 --> 00:09:30.180
could it have been better,

00:09:30.480 --> 00:09:32.840
or maybe you could have lost to Denver?

00:09:33.020 --> 00:09:34.160
It could have been better,

00:09:35.720 --> 00:09:37.460
they lost 7 games,

00:09:37.820 --> 00:09:40.820
you're pretty even with that team,

00:09:42.360 --> 00:09:43.320
in the end,

00:09:44.220 --> 00:09:46.360
those guys played better and better,

00:09:46.560 --> 00:09:49.540
we had our chances in the beginning,

00:09:49.720 --> 00:09:52.300
we lost the first game,

00:09:52.500 --> 00:09:54.200
we won the whole game,

00:09:55.540 --> 00:09:56.980
we had an advantage,

00:09:57.740 --> 00:09:59.420
30 seconds to the end,

00:09:59.560 --> 00:10:00.800
we went into overtime,

00:10:01.000 --> 00:10:01.780
they're a home team,

00:10:01.900 --> 00:10:02.820
an experienced team,

00:10:02.960 --> 00:10:03.860
they know how to win,

00:10:03.860 --> 00:10:07.100
they got the game

00:10:08.520 --> 00:10:10.320
we were supposed to get,

00:10:10.980 --> 00:10:12.440
and in the 4th game,

00:10:13.040 --> 00:10:14.920
Erron Gordon was in for a win,

00:10:15.540 --> 00:10:16.540
with the passing of time,

00:10:18.760 --> 00:10:20.280
when Jokic missed,

00:10:20.760 --> 00:10:24.240
he was perfect for that putback

00:10:24.240 --> 00:10:25.720
that Erron Gordon made,

00:10:26.500 --> 00:10:28.260
where the ball might have moved a little,

00:10:28.540 --> 00:10:29.820
it wouldn't have come to that,

00:10:29.880 --> 00:10:30.960
it would have gone into overtime,

00:10:31.200 --> 00:10:32.940
and we only had momentum,

00:10:33.760 --> 00:10:33.860
that's how it was,

00:10:33.860 --> 00:10:34.100
so,

00:10:35.340 --> 00:10:38.180
we had our chances in those two games,

00:10:38.460 --> 00:10:40.480
if we had won one of those two,

00:10:40.540 --> 00:10:41.960
I think we would have won the series,

00:10:42.160 --> 00:10:42.380
but,

00:10:42.780 --> 00:10:45.900
it's hard to say what would have happened,

00:10:45.980 --> 00:10:46.680
if it had happened,

00:10:47.660 --> 00:10:48.220
we lost,

00:10:49.680 --> 00:10:50.660
everything was fair,

00:10:51.760 --> 00:10:52.160
unfortunately,

00:10:52.640 --> 00:10:53.560
that's how the NBA works,

00:10:54.640 --> 00:10:55.600
small details,

00:10:55.860 --> 00:10:57.720
the difference between losing the first round

00:10:57.720 --> 00:10:58.840
and winning the title,

00:10:59.040 --> 00:11:01.100
so, nothing,

00:11:03.860 --> 00:11:03.960
it's a game,

00:11:04.760 --> 00:11:05.380
it's a game,

00:11:06.100 --> 00:11:06.640
and above all,

00:11:06.880 --> 00:11:07.760
your games were great,

00:11:09.020 --> 00:11:10.520
did you limit Jokic?

00:11:12.220 --> 00:11:14.260
Well, I think I limited him,

00:11:14.440 --> 00:11:17.180
he has great stats,

00:11:19.040 --> 00:11:21.460
it's hard to stop him,

00:11:21.580 --> 00:11:23.100
you have to try to limit him,

00:11:23.260 --> 00:11:24.960
you have to try to make it harder for him,

00:11:25.040 --> 00:11:26.040
whatever he does,

00:11:26.240 --> 00:11:26.520
he scores,

00:11:27.300 --> 00:11:28.440
he adds, he jumps,

00:11:28.820 --> 00:11:29.100
he runs,

00:11:29.280 --> 00:11:30.920
you have to try to make it harder for him,

00:11:36.980 --> 00:11:43.560
He's the best player in the world today, so it's hard to stop him.

00:11:43.680 --> 00:11:46.220
You have to try to limit everything and make it harder for him.

00:11:46.620 --> 00:11:53.580
I think he can do that best in the NBA.

00:11:53.920 --> 00:11:55.400
He's one of the best in that.

00:11:55.400 --> 00:12:02.580
I think I know how he thinks about certain situations.

00:12:02.760 --> 00:12:13.400
I know that he has an advantage in America, with his height, height, weight, physicality.

00:12:13.600 --> 00:12:15.280
I know that he can parry that.

00:12:16.120 --> 00:12:17.280
It's really hard.

00:12:18.740 --> 00:12:21.480
He's a real star, he has a solution for everything.

00:12:21.480 --> 00:12:25.160
He just tries to make it a bit harder for him.

00:12:26.000 --> 00:12:28.880
It's hard for him to prepare, regardless of all the video analysis.

00:12:30.620 --> 00:12:36.260
Is he the hardest player in the NBA, but also in our area?

00:12:37.540 --> 00:12:38.940
For sure, for me for sure.

00:12:39.080 --> 00:12:41.020
I don't know how it is for others, but for me for sure.

00:12:42.480 --> 00:12:47.140
As I said before, he's not...

00:12:47.140 --> 00:12:51.040
Everything you learn as a center forward in your career, defense,

00:12:51.580 --> 00:12:53.720
it all falls into place when you play against him.

00:12:54.000 --> 00:12:57.740
He plays in a way that other centers don't play.

00:12:57.800 --> 00:13:02.000
He leads the ball in the pick and roll, and puts the block in the pick and roll.

00:13:02.100 --> 00:13:06.320
He can catch, he can roll, he can attack with his face, his back,

00:13:06.820 --> 00:13:08.860
he puts the pin down behind him.

00:13:09.520 --> 00:13:12.520
It really changes the philosophy.

00:13:12.580 --> 00:13:14.820
You have to prepare to guard your back,

00:13:15.860 --> 00:13:18.220
and as a center forward, you never guard your back.

00:13:20.120 --> 00:13:22.860
They play randomly.

00:13:23.800 --> 00:13:25.420
He plays, and so does the Denver team,

00:13:25.660 --> 00:13:29.100
so it's hard to scout and watch videos,

00:13:29.200 --> 00:13:31.840
because they have solutions for every defense.

00:13:32.260 --> 00:13:36.520
It's not easy, you have to be quick in your head,

00:13:36.520 --> 00:13:40.000
and adapt quickly.

00:13:40.260 --> 00:13:43.780
Speaking of quick thinking, quick reactions,

00:13:44.200 --> 00:13:45.740
we need coach Lua Staken.

00:13:46.020 --> 00:13:47.300
Steve Wisher is on the doorstep.

00:13:48.540 --> 00:13:52.900
He has a great preparation, and I'm sure it affected your season.

00:13:53.280 --> 00:13:54.060
Yes, for sure.

00:13:55.180 --> 00:13:56.560
I'm in constant contact with him,

00:13:57.040 --> 00:13:59.360
and I should have visited Croatia this summer.

00:14:01.760 --> 00:14:05.220
He's the best coach I've ever had,

00:14:05.220 --> 00:14:07.880
and we have a good relationship.

00:14:08.760 --> 00:14:12.120
We talk before and after the game,

00:14:12.320 --> 00:14:14.040
we discuss tactics.

00:14:14.940 --> 00:14:15.800
He trusts me a lot.

00:14:18.320 --> 00:14:20.980
He's quick to think about the game,

00:14:21.440 --> 00:14:23.720
he adapts quickly,

00:14:23.840 --> 00:14:26.120
he sees something, and he's ready to adapt.

00:14:27.660 --> 00:14:28.860
He's a real expert.

00:14:29.300 --> 00:14:31.080
I've never worked with a coach like him,

00:14:31.080 --> 00:14:36.140
and I have a great relationship with him.

00:14:36.680 --> 00:14:39.560
I hope I'll play for him as long as I can.

00:14:40.020 --> 00:14:42.220
Considering all your statistics,

00:14:43.120 --> 00:14:45.140
and your progress this season,

00:14:45.940 --> 00:14:48.620
who do you have chemistry with the most?

00:14:48.720 --> 00:14:51.600
Who sees you the most in those pick-and-roll situations?

00:14:52.080 --> 00:14:52.620
Harden.

00:14:53.800 --> 00:14:56.820
Ever since he came to our team last season,

00:14:59.560 --> 00:15:01.060
we immediately created a team.

00:15:01.060 --> 00:15:01.900
He has a great chemistry.

00:15:03.760 --> 00:15:06.880
His basketball IQ is amazing.

00:15:09.860 --> 00:15:12.780
He thinks in a totally different way.

00:15:13.440 --> 00:15:16.580
He knows who likes what,

00:15:17.060 --> 00:15:19.560
in which position he likes the ball,

00:15:20.340 --> 00:15:21.520
what he's going to do,

00:15:22.380 --> 00:15:23.900
he sees it all through the video.

00:15:25.140 --> 00:15:28.180
He really prepares a lot for those games.

00:15:30.540 --> 00:15:34.120
I'm a play-center,

00:15:34.240 --> 00:15:35.210
so I have to have that connection.

00:15:36.080 --> 00:15:37.800
When you have a player like him,

00:15:38.440 --> 00:15:39.420
it's not that hard.

00:15:39.580 --> 00:15:41.580
You have to be smart, you have to read the defense,

00:15:41.780 --> 00:15:43.480
you have to know how to set the pick,

00:15:43.580 --> 00:15:48.080
where to roll, and he'll do most of the work.

00:15:49.080 --> 00:15:51.120
I have the biggest chemistry with him.

00:15:51.840 --> 00:15:54.860
He's like a leader, a worker.

00:15:56.020 --> 00:15:57.540
I've seen a lot of your statements,

00:15:57.600 --> 00:15:59.540
where you said that he's an insane worker,

00:15:59.680 --> 00:16:01.260
that he comes back after every summer,

00:16:02.400 --> 00:16:04.440
as if he never stopped playing.

00:16:04.520 --> 00:16:07.880
No, no, he's a player.

00:16:09.520 --> 00:16:11.140
When you play with him,

00:16:11.220 --> 00:16:13.780
when you see every game, every possession,

00:16:15.520 --> 00:16:18.380
how much the other players respect him,

00:16:18.480 --> 00:16:21.180
not just him, the stars of other teams,

00:16:21.180 --> 00:16:23.580
how much fear they have against him,

00:16:23.680 --> 00:16:26.220
when he's in defense, how they don't want to keep him,

00:16:26.660 --> 00:16:27.780
when he's in attack.

00:16:28.560 --> 00:16:31.340
It's impressive to see,

00:16:31.620 --> 00:16:34.160
but he did it all with work.

00:16:34.360 --> 00:16:38.420
He didn't enter the NBA as a top-five pick,

00:16:38.600 --> 00:16:41.420
the biggest talent, but as a defensive player,

00:16:42.360 --> 00:16:43.200
a role-player.

00:16:43.600 --> 00:16:45.320
He did it all with his work.

00:16:45.320 --> 00:16:48.120
He's an insane worker.

00:16:49.740 --> 00:16:52.680
Every day, the same training, the same training.

00:16:52.860 --> 00:16:54.500
It's not a crazy rhythm,

00:16:54.680 --> 00:16:57.540
he knows what positions he'll get the ball,

00:16:57.720 --> 00:17:00.320
what his shots will be, he just works on it.

00:17:00.520 --> 00:17:03.319
It's hours and hours of work every day,

00:17:04.300 --> 00:17:05.660
non-stop training.

00:17:06.220 --> 00:17:08.180
I think it shows.

00:17:09.079 --> 00:17:10.780
He won the title twice,

00:17:10.780 --> 00:17:14.339
he won the MVP final twice.

00:17:15.220 --> 00:17:17.660
There's not much to say about him.

00:17:19.099 --> 00:17:22.140
We also have to mention Bogdanović.

00:17:23.319 --> 00:17:25.619
I've read a lot about his interviews,

00:17:25.839 --> 00:17:27.660
and everyone mentions your role,

00:17:28.080 --> 00:17:30.620
how he thanked you, how you received him.

00:17:31.080 --> 00:17:33.960
How glad you are that a player

00:17:33.960 --> 00:17:37.120
from our speaking area came,

00:17:37.120 --> 00:17:41.520
and how they immediately went out on the field

00:17:41.520 --> 00:17:42.380
to celebrate.

00:17:45.160 --> 00:17:49.380
I didn't even know how much it meant

00:17:49.880 --> 00:17:50.820
to play there for nine years.

00:17:52.100 --> 00:17:58.400
I've never had anyone from our speaking area

00:17:58.400 --> 00:17:58.500
to talk the same language,

00:17:58.500 --> 00:18:00.200
to have the same mentality,

00:18:00.440 --> 00:18:02.520
to go through the same basketball school,

00:18:04.280 --> 00:18:08.960
I think it meant a lot to me.

00:18:09.060 --> 00:18:09.980
I think it meant a lot to him.

00:18:10.760 --> 00:18:13.640
From the moment we found out about the trade,

00:18:13.640 --> 00:18:14.640
we immediately got in touch.

00:18:15.040 --> 00:18:17.400
The next day he came to LA,

00:18:17.460 --> 00:18:18.600
we went out for a drink,

00:18:19.480 --> 00:18:21.420
and we sat next to each other,

00:18:21.680 --> 00:18:24.680
we were out on the field all the time,

00:18:24.720 --> 00:18:25.940
we hung out at his place,

00:18:25.940 --> 00:18:28.100
we would go out for dinners,

00:18:28.850 --> 00:18:31.840
we really clicked,

00:18:32.280 --> 00:18:34.300
and it showed on the field.

00:18:34.640 --> 00:18:37.940
He and I were great on the field,

00:18:38.700 --> 00:18:39.300
we had a lot of fun,

00:18:40.640 --> 00:18:42.260
it was really nice for us,

00:18:44.160 --> 00:18:45.820
the chemistry was great,

00:18:45.860 --> 00:18:48.040
but with our relationship,

00:18:48.380 --> 00:18:51.540
everyone got excited about us,

00:18:51.540 --> 00:18:54.620
and he brought us a lot when he came.

00:18:54.920 --> 00:18:56.460
Did the music change in Slačionica?

00:18:57.000 --> 00:18:59.400
Well, yes, here and there.

00:19:00.340 --> 00:19:03.920
We mostly adapt our music to the Americans,

00:19:04.020 --> 00:19:05.880
here and there on the plane,

00:19:06.060 --> 00:19:09.160
we can play some of our stuff,

00:19:09.520 --> 00:19:11.360
but when we are alone,

00:19:11.640 --> 00:19:15.020
we can play more of our music,

00:19:15.140 --> 00:19:17.560
and in Slačionica, here and there,

00:19:17.560 --> 00:19:19.320
we have our days where we play music,

00:19:19.520 --> 00:19:21.780
and we have our days where we listen to American music.

00:19:22.100 --> 00:19:23.020
You have been in LA for 9 years,

00:19:24.340 --> 00:19:26.220
a life away from the field.

00:19:28.560 --> 00:19:30.640
Yes, 9 years went by quickly,

00:19:32.640 --> 00:19:34.420
I could never have imagined

00:19:34.420 --> 00:19:37.500
that I would live in LA,

00:19:37.960 --> 00:19:39.600
and that I would stay there for 9 years.

00:19:40.380 --> 00:19:42.020
It rarely happens in the NBA

00:19:42.020 --> 00:19:44.680
that someone can stay in one place for a long time,

00:19:44.940 --> 00:19:49.140
I am lucky that it happened to me,

00:19:50.240 --> 00:19:52.680
life is phenomenal,

00:19:53.840 --> 00:19:55.880
the weather is always great,

00:19:56.240 --> 00:19:58.480
it's not cold, it's not too hot,

00:19:58.660 --> 00:20:00.720
you are next to the ocean,

00:20:01.200 --> 00:20:02.080
there are beaches,

00:20:02.660 --> 00:20:05.580
you have everything you can wish for,

00:20:07.000 --> 00:20:09.380
from the top restaurants,

00:20:09.380 --> 00:20:12.380
to everything,

00:20:13.440 --> 00:20:15.640
there is everything you can imagine,

00:20:16.480 --> 00:20:19.440
it's like the center of the world,

00:20:20.220 --> 00:20:21.620
and I am really satisfied,

00:20:21.820 --> 00:20:23.300
I would love to spend as long as possible there.

00:20:23.480 --> 00:20:24.920
Your wife is your biggest support,

00:20:25.100 --> 00:20:26.340
she is also into sports,

00:20:26.940 --> 00:20:28.220
for those who don't know,

00:20:30.220 --> 00:20:34.920
she loves the most noble animals.

00:20:34.920 --> 00:20:39.320
Yes, my wife is with me all the time,

00:20:39.420 --> 00:20:41.000
she has been living in the US since I was born,

00:20:41.800 --> 00:20:44.760
I don't know how I could live there without her,

00:20:45.160 --> 00:20:46.920
she is a great support,

00:20:48.760 --> 00:20:51.040
she makes my life easier,

00:20:53.040 --> 00:20:55.880
it's hard to do anything in the US,

00:20:56.560 --> 00:20:57.560
it's hard to do anything,

00:21:00.220 --> 00:21:02.060
when you go on a trip,

00:21:02.980 --> 00:21:04.340
you spend 2 weeks there,

00:21:04.340 --> 00:21:05.980
and when you come back,

00:21:06.600 --> 00:21:09.380
it means a lot that someone is waiting for you at home,

00:21:09.500 --> 00:21:13.700
it means a lot to me,

00:21:15.080 --> 00:21:17.820
and she is also into cross-country skiing.

00:21:17.820 --> 00:21:18.280
Yes, I saw that,

00:21:20.060 --> 00:21:23.440
she is doing quite well,

00:21:23.500 --> 00:21:28.540
we even raise horses from that sport,

00:21:29.300 --> 00:21:30.340
horses in Slavonia,

00:21:32.740 --> 00:21:36.100
we support each other in sports,

00:21:36.320 --> 00:21:38.160
we are each other's biggest support,

00:21:38.600 --> 00:21:40.320
and it works out well for us.

00:21:40.360 --> 00:21:41.040
And who cooks at home?

00:21:42.080 --> 00:21:42.860
She cooks at home,

00:21:43.420 --> 00:21:48.580
in the last 2 years,

00:21:49.520 --> 00:21:50.900
we have a cook,

00:21:51.620 --> 00:21:54.340
where she cooks a bit more,

00:21:56.080 --> 00:21:57.760
according to some program,

00:21:57.760 --> 00:22:03.320
there are some details,

00:22:03.640 --> 00:22:05.920
that you think are not important,

00:22:05.940 --> 00:22:07.280
but they are really important,

00:22:09.600 --> 00:22:12.180
and they help you on the field,

00:22:12.380 --> 00:22:13.780
you feel a lot better,

00:22:14.760 --> 00:22:15.960
and you are healthier,

00:22:17.240 --> 00:22:20.820
and when our kitchen is missing,

00:22:20.820 --> 00:22:21.880
she cooks for us,

00:22:21.960 --> 00:22:24.540
so we find that balance.

00:22:26.420 --> 00:22:29.140
You came before the riots,

00:22:29.480 --> 00:22:31.360
how much did you follow it?

00:22:31.660 --> 00:22:33.000
I followed it, of course,

00:22:33.160 --> 00:22:34.760
I ask people what is happening,

00:22:36.260 --> 00:22:36.680
unfortunately,

00:22:38.420 --> 00:22:42.840
because of those criminals who came,

00:22:43.120 --> 00:22:45.840
and who are trying to solve it,

00:22:45.940 --> 00:22:48.060
unfortunately, they are the biggest victims,

00:22:48.240 --> 00:22:52.420
people who are in LA for 20-30 years,

00:22:52.420 --> 00:22:55.500
people who built that life,

00:22:55.640 --> 00:22:57.600
unfortunately, they never got the papers,

00:22:57.760 --> 00:22:59.820
but they have children and grandchildren,

00:23:00.080 --> 00:23:02.660
unfortunately, they separate those people

00:23:02.660 --> 00:23:03.860
from their families,

00:23:04.520 --> 00:23:06.520
it is a very difficult situation.

00:23:08.720 --> 00:23:11.500
How did you survive that terrible fire?

00:23:12.220 --> 00:23:14.880
I contacted some of your friends from Chitlka,

00:23:14.900 --> 00:23:16.820
and they told me that you haven't been in touch for a few days.

00:23:18.560 --> 00:23:22.040
It was terrible what was happening.

00:23:22.800 --> 00:23:23.740
It looked apocalyptic.

00:23:24.080 --> 00:23:27.600
Yes, those winds were so strong

00:23:27.600 --> 00:23:29.960
that they couldn't lift the canoes,

00:23:30.140 --> 00:23:30.900
the helicopters,

00:23:30.900 --> 00:23:33.780
there was no water,

00:23:34.400 --> 00:23:38.560
which is a big problem for the government,

00:23:39.060 --> 00:23:39.820
and the administration,

00:23:40.900 --> 00:23:43.280
people couldn't put out the houses,

00:23:43.280 --> 00:23:44.980
there was no fire extinguisher,

00:23:45.080 --> 00:23:46.280
they couldn't put it out,

00:23:47.240 --> 00:23:49.060
they just let it burn,

00:23:49.180 --> 00:23:50.460
they couldn't do anything,

00:23:50.640 --> 00:23:52.820
the winds were unbearable,

00:23:53.120 --> 00:23:56.180
it came pretty close to the house,

00:23:56.500 --> 00:23:58.420
we didn't even sleep for two nights,

00:23:59.040 --> 00:24:00.500
we only watched the news,

00:24:01.960 --> 00:24:03.380
how close it was,

00:24:03.380 --> 00:24:05.800
we didn't know if we should evacuate.

00:24:07.060 --> 00:24:07.900
Thank God,

00:24:09.840 --> 00:24:11.360
we didn't burn the house,

00:24:11.500 --> 00:24:15.220
but unfortunately, a lot of people had to be evacuated,

00:24:15.900 --> 00:24:17.040
they burned their houses,

00:24:17.220 --> 00:24:19.040
some of them didn't even burn their houses,

00:24:19.200 --> 00:24:21.760
but the winds in those settlements were unbearable.

00:24:23.820 --> 00:24:27.040
We mentioned Ivica Bogdana Bogdanović,

00:24:27.720 --> 00:24:29.880
how often do you hear about Bojan Bogdanović?

00:24:29.880 --> 00:24:34.200
Often, Bojan helped me a lot

00:24:34.200 --> 00:24:35.860
when I went to America,

00:24:36.260 --> 00:24:37.520
with his advice,

00:24:37.820 --> 00:24:38.620
socializing,

00:24:41.580 --> 00:24:43.180
we played together,

00:24:44.840 --> 00:24:46.400
we are often in touch,

00:24:48.020 --> 00:24:49.940
all our players are there,

00:24:50.840 --> 00:24:52.880
we are all great, we all hang out,

00:24:53.240 --> 00:24:55.140
so we are in touch a lot.

00:24:55.140 --> 00:24:56.580
At one point,

00:24:58.400 --> 00:25:00.840
one Hercegovacka Petorka could be formed,

00:25:00.920 --> 00:25:01.680
Bojan,

00:25:04.600 --> 00:25:06.260
Karlo Matković,

00:25:06.820 --> 00:25:07.580
Bender,

00:25:10.130 --> 00:25:12.460
what is it in our area?

00:25:14.100 --> 00:25:19.400
I think that we are born and raised

00:25:19.400 --> 00:25:20.900
in a different way

00:25:20.900 --> 00:25:23.080
than anywhere else in the world,

00:25:23.080 --> 00:25:24.800
we are a bit tougher,

00:25:26.440 --> 00:25:27.600
stronger in the head,

00:25:28.920 --> 00:25:29.860
we are stronger in everything,

00:25:31.180 --> 00:25:35.400
we are stronger in Hercegovac,

00:25:35.720 --> 00:25:37.220
I think that is number one,

00:25:37.320 --> 00:25:39.380
number two is our physicality,

00:25:39.680 --> 00:25:42.640
that we are one of the greatest people in the world,

00:25:43.440 --> 00:25:46.400
we are not weak,

00:25:46.660 --> 00:25:50.040
that is the first prerequisite

00:25:50.040 --> 00:25:51.220
to be able to do something,

00:25:51.820 --> 00:25:52.300
we have talent,

00:25:53.580 --> 00:25:58.360
I am always sad that there is not so much investment in sports,

00:25:59.040 --> 00:26:00.300
there are not so many resources,

00:26:00.580 --> 00:26:03.260
because I think there would be a lot more players,

00:26:03.340 --> 00:26:05.080
it is a really hard road to that,

00:26:06.020 --> 00:26:08.440
to that NBA career,

00:26:08.580 --> 00:26:09.880
not only NBA career,

00:26:10.020 --> 00:26:13.280
European career, it is a hard road,

00:26:13.280 --> 00:26:14.780
we have to overcome that,

00:26:15.940 --> 00:26:19.360
but we have some physical prerequisites,

00:26:20.560 --> 00:26:24.180
but unfortunately we do not have enough people there,

00:26:24.480 --> 00:26:25.940
and resources in sports,

00:26:26.700 --> 00:26:29.480
and I think that there would be a lot more players

00:26:29.480 --> 00:26:32.100
with top careers than here,

00:26:32.200 --> 00:26:33.380
that we have those things.

00:26:33.720 --> 00:26:35.500
When we already touched on Bojan,

00:26:36.320 --> 00:26:38.040
one for the fans,

00:26:38.040 --> 00:26:40.020
and for you as well,

00:26:40.060 --> 00:26:41.360
a painful topic, the national team,

00:26:43.640 --> 00:26:46.760
what is the problem?

00:26:47.240 --> 00:26:49.800
The national team is not lacking,

00:26:50.220 --> 00:26:52.520
not in Croatia, not in football,

00:26:52.880 --> 00:26:53.980
not in basketball, not in basketball,

00:26:54.720 --> 00:26:57.080
some other countries have a problem with NBA players,

00:26:57.520 --> 00:26:58.840
with Bojan, Bojan from Garovo,

00:26:58.900 --> 00:27:02.640
until his last game, he wanted more success with the national team

00:27:02.640 --> 00:27:03.200
than anything else,

00:27:04.500 --> 00:27:07.140
you were always available,

00:27:08.480 --> 00:27:11.440
Šarić, always, captain from Garovo for Croatia,

00:27:11.480 --> 00:27:13.380
what is the problem,

00:27:13.520 --> 00:27:16.660
not to reach a top result?

00:27:17.040 --> 00:27:21.480
I think that Bojan is our best player

00:27:21.480 --> 00:27:22.380
for the national team,

00:27:22.540 --> 00:27:24.060
when he played,

00:27:29.480 --> 00:27:31.400
when he was at his peak,

00:27:32.020 --> 00:27:33.840
we were not ready,

00:27:34.800 --> 00:27:35.780
the younger ones,

00:27:36.600 --> 00:27:39.180
and when it came to us being ready,

00:27:39.320 --> 00:27:40.680
he was also at his peak,

00:27:42.680 --> 00:27:46.300
FIBA has a qualifier for every championship in the middle of the season,

00:27:46.520 --> 00:27:48.800
where we, NBA players, cannot play.

00:27:49.480 --> 00:27:51.000
It is impossible for me now,

00:27:51.320 --> 00:27:55.600
this season you have a qualifier in the 11th month,

00:27:56.500 --> 00:27:57.860
you have it in the 2nd month,

00:28:00.500 --> 00:28:06.220
I am obligated to play in the NBA,

00:28:06.520 --> 00:28:07.820
we have a season there,

00:28:09.740 --> 00:28:12.200
I have no choice,

00:28:12.580 --> 00:28:13.920
I cannot play.

00:28:14.520 --> 00:28:16.360
Small countries like Croatia,

00:28:17.320 --> 00:28:19.460
with a small pool of those players,

00:28:20.920 --> 00:28:22.120
it is not enough,

00:28:22.240 --> 00:28:23.440
what you have available,

00:28:23.720 --> 00:28:24.640
it is not enough.

00:28:24.640 --> 00:28:26.360
It is easier for big countries,

00:28:27.020 --> 00:28:29.160
who have a bigger pool of players,

00:28:29.860 --> 00:28:32.180
it is easier for them when NBA players do not play,

00:28:32.940 --> 00:28:34.880
they have more players to choose from,

00:28:35.320 --> 00:28:37.300
and they can qualify,

00:28:37.700 --> 00:28:42.520
but unfortunately, we as a small country cannot.

00:28:42.740 --> 00:28:45.520
I am 28 years old,

00:28:45.760 --> 00:28:47.720
I played one big championship,

00:28:48.760 --> 00:28:49.460
and that is it,

00:28:49.460 --> 00:28:51.120
and who knows when the next time will be,

00:28:51.180 --> 00:28:53.460
this year I did not play in the EuroBasket,

00:28:53.660 --> 00:28:55.440
and I am really sorry that I cannot play

00:28:55.440 --> 00:28:57.740
after my best season so far,

00:28:58.540 --> 00:29:02.040
that I cannot show it on a representative level,

00:29:02.220 --> 00:29:03.320
and I cannot represent the country,

00:29:03.540 --> 00:29:07.640
I do not know what will change there,

00:29:09.040 --> 00:29:11.040
but in the summer it is free,

00:29:11.200 --> 00:29:14.540
and only in the 27th month there is a world championship,

00:29:14.540 --> 00:29:16.880
and it is not easy,

00:29:21.100 --> 00:29:21.580
unfortunately,

00:29:22.040 --> 00:29:23.200
unfortunately it is like that,

00:29:23.380 --> 00:29:25.380
it is a painful point for me,

00:29:26.260 --> 00:29:30.080
and as a child I dream that Croatia will bring a medal

00:29:30.080 --> 00:29:32.360
to any championship,

00:29:32.600 --> 00:29:35.000
but they cannot bring a medal,

00:29:35.140 --> 00:29:39.260
they cannot help when we cannot get to those championships,

00:29:39.500 --> 00:29:40.640
and because of those qualifiers,

00:29:40.640 --> 00:29:44.640
I cannot play,

00:29:44.640 --> 00:29:45.660
I cannot help,

00:29:45.760 --> 00:29:49.000
and unfortunately it is like that,

00:29:49.180 --> 00:29:51.480
I hope that something will change around that,

00:29:51.800 --> 00:29:54.240
but for now it is like that.

00:29:54.440 --> 00:29:55.960
On the other hand, the clubs are,

00:29:56.480 --> 00:29:58.820
you played in Cibona, Cibona is on its knees,

00:29:59.800 --> 00:30:02.080
Zadar, let's say, has continuity,

00:30:02.420 --> 00:30:05.940
some results, I think,

00:30:05.940 --> 00:30:08.700
I am surprised because others are not on the same level,

00:30:09.260 --> 00:30:12.600
Split is trying something with its school,

00:30:12.760 --> 00:30:13.620
with a young story,

00:30:14.200 --> 00:30:17.580
but there is no way for three players to come out of it,

00:30:17.580 --> 00:30:19.480
who could maybe pass through those qualifiers,

00:30:20.680 --> 00:30:22.540
and then you come to help them.

00:30:22.660 --> 00:30:27.100
I think the league is really weak,

00:30:27.180 --> 00:30:28.360
never bad,

00:30:28.660 --> 00:30:30.980
and I think the clubs are,

00:30:30.980 --> 00:30:35.280
I think Zadar has the most serious club,

00:30:35.420 --> 00:30:36.440
and the best results,

00:30:36.900 --> 00:30:39.100
but I think that is because

00:30:40.000 --> 00:30:42.380
the rest of the league is like that,

00:30:42.880 --> 00:30:46.880
and it is really sad to see Cibona in this state,

00:30:47.280 --> 00:30:49.040
they are coming out of the league for the first time,

00:30:49.220 --> 00:30:50.320
after the league was recorded,

00:30:50.660 --> 00:30:53.920
that they will not play, they will play ABA 2,

00:30:54.080 --> 00:30:56.480
I don't know what the situation will be, but they came out.

00:30:56.480 --> 00:30:59.340
It is really sad to see

00:30:59.340 --> 00:31:00.840
where it all came from,

00:31:01.020 --> 00:31:04.620
when I was a kid, when I played for Cibona,

00:31:05.580 --> 00:31:07.660
already then it went down,

00:31:08.220 --> 00:31:10.780
and then they looked at it all badly,

00:31:10.900 --> 00:31:12.140
and talked about it,

00:31:13.400 --> 00:31:15.560
and then 10 years later, 15 years later,

00:31:15.620 --> 00:31:21.100
when you look 100 times up,

00:31:21.320 --> 00:31:24.800
and you think how the situation was then,

00:31:24.800 --> 00:31:26.740
it was great for us towards this,

00:31:26.920 --> 00:31:28.640
so I don't know,

00:31:28.980 --> 00:31:32.780
the clubs, our domestic league should be thrown out,

00:31:32.920 --> 00:31:35.000
create some players who would carry

00:31:37.100 --> 00:31:38.300
those qualifications,

00:31:39.480 --> 00:31:42.060
but unfortunately the rest of the league is like that,

00:31:42.120 --> 00:31:47.020
and I just hope it will be better.

00:31:48.080 --> 00:31:50.520
Last season, we already talked,

00:31:51.720 --> 00:31:54.020
what are the expectations for the next season,

00:31:54.020 --> 00:31:55.940
and for the future, as far as you are concerned?

00:31:56.720 --> 00:31:59.800
Well, I set some goals,

00:32:00.080 --> 00:32:02.880
I don't know how real they are,

00:32:02.960 --> 00:32:05.500
but that's how my whole life was,

00:32:05.600 --> 00:32:07.800
where I set some goals,

00:32:08.400 --> 00:32:10.760
where everyone talked about it being impossible,

00:32:11.500 --> 00:32:14.000
so I managed to do something,

00:32:14.960 --> 00:32:17.120
my goal is to become an all-star,

00:32:17.820 --> 00:32:19.640
whether that will be next season,

00:32:19.640 --> 00:32:21.720
or until the end of my career,

00:32:21.960 --> 00:32:25.660
that would be my biggest individual goal,

00:32:26.260 --> 00:32:30.200
I would like to be a defensive player for a year,

00:32:30.940 --> 00:32:32.280
first fifth of the season,

00:32:32.460 --> 00:32:35.760
I really have a lot of individual goals,

00:32:35.760 --> 00:32:36.620
that I set,

00:32:36.880 --> 00:32:39.680
I think I'm not far from that,

00:32:40.260 --> 00:32:41.580
but I need more work,

00:32:42.760 --> 00:32:47.680
and dedication to what I will do this summer,

00:32:48.580 --> 00:32:53.420
so I hope that will be the next step in my career,

00:32:53.520 --> 00:32:54.640
next season,

00:32:55.480 --> 00:32:57.660
if not next, next year,

00:32:57.840 --> 00:33:00.520
that's how I set some goals,

00:33:00.620 --> 00:33:02.780
and I think I'm really close to that,

00:33:03.400 --> 00:33:04.400
that I need a little more,

00:33:05.200 --> 00:33:09.280
but of course, that's one goal, to win the NBA title.

00:33:10.020 --> 00:33:12.180
You've been in the Clippers since 2019,

00:33:12.580 --> 00:33:13.200
if I'm not mistaken,

00:33:15.980 --> 00:33:17.220
NBA is unpredictable,

00:33:17.420 --> 00:33:22.600
when do you think you'll be in the Clippers?

00:33:23.820 --> 00:33:25.960
I have a contract for another three years,

00:33:26.380 --> 00:33:29.260
so I hope for a long time,

00:33:29.980 --> 00:33:31.620
you never know in the NBA,

00:33:34.200 --> 00:33:35.400
it's business first,

00:33:36.100 --> 00:33:39.480
and you never know what can happen,

00:33:39.940 --> 00:33:42.700
maybe they can be too satisfied with you,

00:33:42.960 --> 00:33:43.180
but you never know,

00:33:43.180 --> 00:33:44.780
maybe they got an offer for you,

00:33:44.920 --> 00:33:47.200
and that's business,

00:33:48.380 --> 00:33:51.000
maybe they changed the whole philosophy of the team,

00:33:51.240 --> 00:33:52.300
what's their goal,

00:33:55.760 --> 00:33:57.700
so you never know,

00:33:58.440 --> 00:34:00.520
what can happen,

00:34:00.680 --> 00:34:01.760
you can't give up,

00:34:01.920 --> 00:34:03.080
I think you're sure,

00:34:04.120 --> 00:34:06.560
trade Luka Dončić showed everyone,

00:34:06.560 --> 00:34:07.900
that no one can touch him,

00:34:08.639 --> 00:34:10.500
players like that never traded,

00:34:11.540 --> 00:34:14.460
everything is possible, you never give up,

00:34:15.960 --> 00:34:17.600
but it's really nice there,

00:34:18.219 --> 00:34:20.360
I enjoy every game,

00:34:20.780 --> 00:34:22.239
I'd like to stay as long as I can.

00:34:22.820 --> 00:34:25.380
As far as the future is concerned,

00:34:25.480 --> 00:34:27.679
we'll look at life after the career,

00:34:27.780 --> 00:34:28.820
that's still far away,

00:34:28.820 --> 00:34:34.100
but do you plan your life in America,

00:34:34.420 --> 00:34:35.500
or maybe Croatia?

00:34:35.980 --> 00:34:36.480
I don't plan,

00:34:36.739 --> 00:34:39.920
there are a hundred things that can happen,

00:34:39.920 --> 00:34:40.820
I still have to play,

00:34:41.699 --> 00:34:46.880
I plan to return to Croatia,

00:34:47.139 --> 00:34:49.600
but for now,

00:34:50.420 --> 00:34:53.679
that's the mentality in my head,

00:34:54.300 --> 00:34:56.120
you can change a hundred things,

00:34:56.840 --> 00:34:57.740
we'll see,

00:34:58.900 --> 00:35:00.460
but as things stand,

00:35:00.620 --> 00:35:02.900
I'd like to live in peace.

00:35:05.860 --> 00:35:07.500
Zagreb-Slavonija-Hercegovina relationship.

00:35:08.140 --> 00:35:08.960
In the end,

00:35:09.520 --> 00:35:11.240
let's go back to the beginning of the story,

00:35:12.060 --> 00:35:15.740
when you and Zoki watched Zoran Planinča,

00:35:16.760 --> 00:35:18.800
as a child you dreamed of being like him,

00:35:18.900 --> 00:35:19.700
to come to the NBA,

00:35:19.700 --> 00:35:21.540
and now we have a situation,

00:35:21.680 --> 00:35:23.520
where Ivan Dodik, a tennis player,

00:35:23.560 --> 00:35:24.560
is working in a center,

00:35:24.800 --> 00:35:30.180
where he will surely make a new Dodik, a new Čilić.

00:35:30.760 --> 00:35:32.960
Will you, after your career,

00:35:34.140 --> 00:35:35.480
not necessarily in that way,

00:35:35.680 --> 00:35:36.900
but with some of your advice,

00:35:40.580 --> 00:35:41.840
direct those children,

00:35:41.960 --> 00:35:45.380
so that tomorrow we get a new Bojan Bogdanović,

00:35:45.380 --> 00:35:48.040
a new Ivica Zubac, a new Zoran Planinča,

00:35:48.320 --> 00:35:50.360
a new Bender, a new Karlo Matković?

00:35:51.100 --> 00:35:52.020
I'd love to,

00:35:52.040 --> 00:35:55.900
I think that's the only right way,

00:35:56.380 --> 00:35:59.920
to give back to others what was given to you.

00:36:00.280 --> 00:36:03.740
I had some motivation from someone else,

00:36:04.420 --> 00:36:06.940
I had some advice, some role model,

00:36:07.080 --> 00:36:09.700
it came from someone else,

00:36:10.620 --> 00:36:12.380
and I really think

00:36:12.380 --> 00:36:16.420
that it would be fair and correct

00:36:16.420 --> 00:36:18.100
to give it back one day,

00:36:18.340 --> 00:36:22.700
to help in some way to younger generations

00:36:22.700 --> 00:36:23.680
and others,

00:36:26.260 --> 00:36:29.920
to be someone's role model or motivation,

00:36:30.140 --> 00:36:31.040
to achieve something,

00:36:31.300 --> 00:36:32.380
to give some advice,

00:36:32.620 --> 00:36:34.780
or to Ivan Dodik, what he's doing,

00:36:34.860 --> 00:36:35.800
it's really great,

00:36:35.800 --> 00:36:41.320
and I think that's a great sign for the future.

00:36:42.100 --> 00:36:45.420
Ivica, thank you for being a guest on our show,

00:36:45.680 --> 00:36:48.260
I wish you a lot of luck in your career,

00:36:48.500 --> 00:36:49.540
and if God allows it,

00:36:49.600 --> 00:36:51.200
see you again in the summer.

00:36:51.620 --> 00:36:54.580
Thank you very much, and if God allows it.

